From yixuan.qiu at cos.name  Tue Feb 17 21:57:13 2015
From: yixuan.qiu at cos.name (Yixuan Qiu)
Date: Tue, 17 Feb 2015 15:57:13 -0500
Subject: [Rcpp-devel] Eigen-like pointer mappings in Rcpp?
In-Reply-To: <1424202822.11887.6.camel@mothra.biostat.mcw.edu>
References: <1424202822.11887.6.camel@mothra.biostat.mcw.edu>
Message-ID: <CAFr_7yHTF8oFmB=ZhdC236SBBEFG2ztmk2P_ot0zpv-nJzAFTQ@mail.gmail.com>

Hello Rodney,
If all you need is to pass a pointer to the fit() function (assuming fit()
does not modify x) and get the result a, you do not need to make a copy.
Simply wrap _x by a NumericVector and call the data() method.

Rcpp::NumericVector x(_x);
double a = fit(x.data(), n);

You can even directly use the R API without creating an Rcpp object.

double a = fit(REAL(_x), n);



Best,
Yixuan





